The polynomials being dealt with here are closely related to the inverse
 of the Cantor function.
 This is perhaps best presented visually.
 Write the binary expansion of a real number 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset 

 as 
\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}
x=\sum_{k=1}^{\infty}\frac{b_{k}}{2^{k}}\label{eq: binary expansion}\end{equation}

\end_inset 

 and then define its Cantorization as 
\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}
