Symbolic dynamics
\layout Standard

The construction and symmetry properties are not limited to continuous curves.
 Any system with a symbolic dynamics in two symbols is naturally parameterized
 through real numbers.
 Consider, for example, the symbolic dynamics of the tent map of unit height.
 By picking an initial value, and then iterating on the tent map, one will
 get a sequence of values.
 For each iteration, write down the letter 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset 

 if the value is less than 1/2, and write the letter 
\begin_inset Formula $B$
\end_inset 

 if the value is more than 1/2.
 The result of the iteration will be an infinitely long string composed
 of the letters 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset 

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $B$
\end_inset 

