\begin_inset Formula $w.$
\end_inset 

 By contrast, 
\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}
t_{w}\left(\frac{1}{3}\right)=\frac{2}{3(1-w)}\label{eq:}\end{equation}

\end_inset 

 has a simple pole at 
\begin_inset Formula $w=1$
\end_inset 

.
 Other values include 
\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}
t_{w}\left(\frac{1}{5}\right)=\frac{2}{5}\cdot\frac{1+2w}{1-w^{2}}\label{eq:}\end{equation}

\end_inset 

and 
\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}
t_{w}\left(\frac{1}{7}\right)=\frac{2}{7}\cdot\frac{1+2w+3w^{2}}{1-w^{3}}\label{eq:}\end{equation}

\end_inset 

